5. Conclusion
There is a circadian variation in autonomic control of HRV that is highly predictive of abnormal pharmacological stress MPI. The non-linear measure Dyx showed the strongest association, suggesting that decreased complexity is a representative feature of dysfunction of cardiac vasomotor regulation, which is likely involves autonomic mechanisms. These hypothesis-generating results should lead to further evaluation of the mechanisms underlying the relationship between autonomic control of HRV and coronary blood ﬂow regulation.
